    <h3>Is an AMC Worth It?</h3>

    <p><strong>AMC is worth it if:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your equipment is 2+ years old and past warranty.</li>
      <li>You rely on the equipment for daily revenue (production ovens, display refrigerators).</li>
      <li>You're in a city where finding reliable independent technicians is difficult.</li>
      <li>The equipment is an imported brand (Sinmag, Rational, Unox) where parts require the authorised network.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>AMC may not be worth it if:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>The equipment is brand new and under manufacturer warranty.</li>
      <li>You have a trusted independent technician who charges reasonable rates.</li>
      <li>The equipment is a low-cost Indian brand where replacement is cheaper than a year of AMC.</li>
      <li>You follow a strict preventive maintenance schedule (detailed below) and the equipment is in good condition.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Always negotiate. AMC prices are not fixed — especially from third-party service companies. If you have multiple pieces of equipment, bundle them for a 15–25% discount. Also, ensure the AMC specifies a maximum response time in writing — "within 24 hours" is standard, but "within 8 hours" is worth paying extra for production-critical equipment.</p>

