    <h2>Equipment Insurance — Protecting Your Investment</h2>

    <p>Equipment insurance is an often-overlooked layer of protection for commercial kitchen owners in India. While AMC covers maintenance and repairs, insurance protects you against catastrophic events — fire, flood, theft, electrical surges, and other events that can destroy equipment worth lakhs.</p>

    <h3>Types of Relevant Insurance</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Standard Fire & Special Perils Policy:</strong> Covers fire, lightning, explosion, storm, flood, earthquake, and malicious damage. This is the most basic coverage — virtually every bakery should have this. Premiums are typically 0.5–1.5% of equipment value per year.</li>
      <li><strong>Machinery Breakdown Insurance:</strong> Specifically covers sudden and unforeseen damage from electrical or mechanical breakdown — voltage surges, short circuits, bearing failures, etc. This is essentially insurance against the kind of catastrophic failures that cost ₹50,000+ to repair. Premiums are typically 1–3% of equipment value per year.</li>
      <li><strong>Business Interruption Insurance:</strong> Covers lost income while equipment is being repaired after an insured event. If your production oven is destroyed in a fire and it takes 6 weeks to replace, this policy covers your lost revenue during that period.</li>
      <li><strong>Electronic Equipment Insurance:</strong> Relevant for high-end digital equipment like Rational combi ovens with connected cooking systems. Covers electronic/digital component failures.</li>
    </ul>

