      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is an AMC contract worth it for bakery equipment? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>For equipment that's past warranty and critical to your daily production — yes, absolutely. A comprehensive AMC (₹10,000–₹18,000/year) typically includes 2–4 preventive visits, priority emergency service, and parts coverage for wear items. Given that a single emergency repair can cost ₹5,000–₹15,000, and downtime costs ₹10,000–₹30,000 per day in lost revenue, an AMC pays for itself if it prevents even one major breakdown per year. However, for low-cost Indian equipment (under ₹50,000), the AMC may cost more than the equipment's annual depreciation — in those cases, a basic non-comprehensive AMC or no AMC may be more sensible.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Why is my commercial oven not heating evenly? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>The most common causes are: a malfunctioning convection fan (not spinning or spinning slowly), overloaded trays blocking air circulation, thermostat calibration drift (temperature sensor reading incorrectly), and worn door gaskets allowing heat to escape from specific points. Start by checking the fan operation, then test with an oven thermometer at different positions inside the oven. If the temperature varies by more than 15°C between positions, the fan or heating element likely needs attention. See our detailed troubleshooting steps in the article above.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How often should I service my commercial refrigerator? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>Condenser coils should be cleaned every 2–4 weeks (this is the single most impactful maintenance task). Door gaskets should be inspected monthly. A full professional service — including refrigerant level check, compressor inspection, and electrical safety check — should be done once a year (twice a year for units in very hot or dusty environments). In Indian conditions, where ambient temperatures reach 40°C+ in summer, the condenser coils accumulate dust and grease much faster than in air-conditioned environments, so biweekly cleaning is recommended during summer months.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Where can I buy spare parts for commercial kitchen equipment in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>The best sources in order of reliability: (1) Your equipment's authorised dealer/distributor — guaranteed genuine parts but 10–30% premium. (2) IndiaMart — India's largest B2B marketplace with thousands of commercial kitchen parts sellers; always verify ratings and ask for brand-specific part numbers. (3) Local electrical wholesale markets — Bhagirath Palace (Delhi), Lohar Chawl (Mumbai), SP Road (Bengaluru) — excellent for motors, relays, capacitors at wholesale rates. (4) Amazon India — good for universal parts with fast delivery. (5) For premium brands like Rational and Unox, critical components (control boards, steam generators) should only be sourced from the manufacturer directly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Should I repair or replace old bakery equipment? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>Use the 50% rule: if a single repair costs more than 50% of what a comparable new/used replacement would cost, replace it. Also consider the equipment's age — most commercial ovens last 8–15 years, and commercial refrigerators last 7–12 years. If your equipment is past 70% of its expected lifespan and needing frequent repairs (more than 2–3 major repairs per year), replacement usually makes more economic sense. Factor in energy efficiency too — a new commercial refrigerator can use 30–40% less electricity than a 10-year-old model. See our <a href="/blog/new-vs-used-bakery-equipment">new vs. used equipment guide</a> for a detailed cost comparison framework.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What's the best brand for after-sales service in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>Among imported brands, Rational (Germany) has the best service infrastructure in India with their own dedicated service team, India-based spare parts warehouse, and 12–24 hour response times in metro cities. Among Indian brands, Blue Star has the widest service network across the country. For the best service-to-price ratio in imported bakery equipment, Sinmag (Taiwan) is hard to beat — they have strong distributor networks in most Indian cities with readily available parts. See our brand service comparison table above for detailed ratings of 10 major brands.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

